B) Output format for the Spelling Variation Layer:
   ---------------------------------------------
Spelling variation layer is a layer above the CORE morph to account for the 
variations in written spellings in Hindi. All the concerned programs are 
in morph_SV directory.
The convention used in the output is:

After the start marker, rule number is appended and then follows the spelling
used for morph analysis followed by the morph analysis of the word with new 
spelling.
e.g. in case of 'badZI' spelling is changed internally to 'badI' and then 
badI is analysed.

final output is:
MO_¤RL 1: badI:1_badI{kAlI adj f any any }/_MO 
     |  |  |
     |  |  |
    Rule # changed spelling
